    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1970-09-21T20:10:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1970-09-21T20:10:00-05:00" n="310"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d310">
                <head>310. Transcript of a Telephone Conversation Between President <persName
                        corresp="#p_NRM1">Nixon</persName> and the President’s Assistant for
                    National Security Affairs (<persName corresp="#p_KHA1"
                        >Kissinger</persName>)<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d310fn1">Source:
                        National Archives, <persName corresp="#p_NRM1">Nixon</persName> Presidential
                        Materials, <persName corresp="#p_KHA1">Kissinger</persName> Telephone
                        Conversations, Box 30, Chronological Files. No classification
                        marking.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1970-09-21T21:10:00-04:00">September 21, 1970, 9:10 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_NRM1">P</persName>: <persName>Henry</persName>, I am going
                    to bed early—I am meeting with Congress in the morning.</p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_KHA1">K</persName>: Think it is going to be quiet tonight.
                    I won’t disturb you unless—</p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_NRM1">P</persName>: If you hear anything, let me know.</p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_KHA1">K</persName>: Haven’t given them the answers. When I
                    talked to <persName corresp="#p_RY1">Rabin</persName>
                    <note n="2" xml:id="d310fn2">See <ref target="#d308">Document 308</ref>.</note>
                    there were so many conflicting signals—I think by tomorrow morning we will have
                    answers.</p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_NRM1">P</persName>: We will have additional intelligence
                    on where it all stands.</p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_KHA1">K</persName>: Think noon tomorrow is a good time for
                    this group to meet.<note n="3" xml:id="d310fn3">See <ref target="#d313">Document
                            313</ref>.</note> I think the Jordanian psychological end is stronger,
                    more than their physical strength.</p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_NRM1">P</persName>: More than they are showing on their
                    nerve.</p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_KHA1">K</persName>: They might still pull it out.</p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_NRM1">P</persName>: I hope so but whatever, if the thing
                    quiets down, this trip<note n="4" xml:id="d310fn4">President <persName
                            corresp="#p_NRM1">Nixon</persName> left Washington on September 27 for a
                        trip to Europe and the United Kingdom.</note> would be a reinforcement.</p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_KHA1">K</persName>: If the Israelis don’t move by
                        Thursday,<note n="5" xml:id="d310fn5">September 24.</note> the thing will
                    settle down.</p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_NRM1">P</persName>: Okay <persName>Henry</persName>.</p>
            </div>
